============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is relativity?
A1: Einstein's relativity: Special (1905) — time dilates,
     mass increases at high speeds; E=mc². General (1915) —
     gravity is curved spacetime; explains black holes and
     expanding universe.

Q2: What is democracy?
A2: Democracy is government where power derives from the
     people through free elections, rule of law, and
     protection of minority rights. Types include direct and
     representative democracy.

Q3: What is the greenhouse effect?
A3: Greenhouse gases (CO2, methane) trap heat radiated from
     Earth's surface. Natural effect warms Earth; human
     emissions intensify it causing climate change.

Q4: What is gravity?
A4: Gravity is an attractive force between all masses.
     Newton described it as F = Gm1m2/r². Einstein refined
     it as spacetime curvature in general relativity.

Q5: What is supply and demand?
A5: Supply and demand determines prices: higher demand or
     lower supply raises prices; lower demand or higher
     supply lowers prices. Equilibrium is where both curves
     intersect.

